summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene (TCE) is discussed in relation to its concentrations and degradation in aquifer wells, while 2-methyl-4-nitroaniline ethylene dimethylammonium is not mentioned or connected to TCE's behavior or degradation processes. The focus is primarily on TCE's environmental fate, with no direct relationship or interaction with the other compound indicated.
